topic.body:
The New Zealand Independence Party:
- Life (Universal Basic Income)
- Liberty (Free Market policies, minimum regulation e.g. Hong Kong)
- The Pursuit of Happiness (Individual liberty e.g. legalized cannabis)
&nbsp;
We believe in a country where the little girl next door can set up a lemonade stand in her front yard without being fined by the council. (Liberty)
&nbsp;
We also believe the little girl next door should have the right to a good night's sleep, and earn pocket money instead of rent money. (UBI)
&nbsp;
We will push New Zealand into the 21st century, a Type I civilization; a Star Trek economy. We will make the barbarism of poverty a thing of the past, while at the same time leading the country into prosperity through Hong Kong-style economics. We oppose nanny state policies - we want bars, casinos, night clubs, cannabis coffee shops and dispensaries, etc. Uber, self-driving cars, robot rubbish collectors, etc. A fun country to live in.
&nbsp;
We may or may not run for parliament, which is a corrupt mafia organization run by overpaid yuppies who take long holidays and play golf all day. We will start our own country within this country; We will crowd-fund our UBI if we have to.
&nbsp;
Should we gain enough momentum to become a major party, we will declare New Zealand a republic. The bi-partisan politics of division isn't working, we can't have policies that pit one group against another group - we need a country that works for Everybody.
